page.title: 01POPULATION
page.content: {Population In our given area today, there are only{two}houses inhabited all the year round. One is the home of a{gamekeeper and stalker; the other is the old station master's house. There is no longer a{stationmaster}at Struan station for the trains from Inverness to Perth and the south no longer stop at Struan. THE Station house is the home of Mr Dow, who works for the {Roads Dept. of Tayside Regional {Council. Mr Reid, the gamekeeper lives at {Clunes(sheet NN 76 NE) 782671.}His family is made up of two sons and one daughter, while Mr Dow's family is made up of two daughters and one son.
